The officer's baby daughter was taken to the hospital to be treated for minor injuries sustained in the fall, but she was released home the next day.

The thwarted robbery came the same day that Brazil’s Department of Public Security released crime statistics for October indicting that the number of robberies and murders in Sao Paulo have gone up compared to the year before.

 

